<h4 class="margin-top">Meet Ramneek and Citi Ventures</h4>

<p>
	Ramneek is Managing Director and Co-head of Global Venture Investing at Citi Ventures. Before Citi, he was a partner at Battery Ventures where he focused on the online-to-offline space and also helped build Battery's India investment efforts. 
</p>

<p>
	Citi Ventures is stage agnostic, however, most of its investments occur after the post product stage so Citi can pilot the product and test proof-of-concepts internally. Typical deals are in the Series A and B stages and may range from $3 to $10 million. Citi Ventures seeks to support its companies in multiple rounds and enjoys bringing new capabilities into its investments. This also requires a certain level of maturity in the business for Citi to be able to add value.
</p>

